RasterFunctionTemplate.Name: Watermap Extent Blue Only
RasterFunctionTemplate.Description: Applies a blue color to cells with a pixel value of 1 (indicating water), and no color to 0 values.

Function.Name: Colormap
Function.Description: Changes pixel values to display the raster data as either a grayscale or a red, green, blue (RGB) image, based on a colormap or a color ramp.

AnyType.Name: Watermap Extent Discrete White and Blue No Color Scheme
AnyType.Description: Applies a blue color to cells with a pixel value of 1 (indicating water) and a 50% transparent white to cells not identified as water.

Function.Name: Stretch
Function.Description: Enhances an image by adjusting the range of values displayed. This does not alter the underlying pixel values. If a pixel has a value outside of the specified range, it will appear as either the minimum or maximum value.
